# Workflow

After implementing any change:

1. Run the project test suite.
2. If a test fails:
   - Do NOT modify the test.
   - Fix the implementation.
3. Only after all tests pass:
   - Create modular commits (one logical change per commit; split large changes into multiple commits).
   - Use conventional commit messages (feat:, fix:, refactor:, etc.).
   - Use branches professionally (feature branches, fix branches; integrate via merge/rebase as defined for the project).

Never bypass failing tests.
